DESCRIPTION: Generates a visualization of a symmetrical Pyramid using the '#' character based on the height input entered by the user.

LOGIC EMPHASIS (CONDITIONALS & BOUNDARIES):

1. Input Validation (Loop Condition):

- Uses the conditional: (height < 1 || height > 8)
- Meaning: The program WILL CONTINUOUSLY repeat requesting input AS LONG AS the height
  value is less than 1 OR greater than 8 (Limiting memory & visual area).

2. Algorithm Boundary Rules (Loop Control Condition):

- Row Condition: (i <= height) -> Controls the total number of staircase levels.
- Space Condition: (j < height - i) -> Reduces spaces as rows increase.
- Block Condition: (j < i) -> Increases the number of '#' as rows increase.
